```php  $myArray = []; $myArray["value"] = 10; // Explicit key $myArray[10] = 20; // Implicit numeric key  //Improved code using isset() to check for key existence. if (isset($myArray[0])) {     echo $myArray[0]; } else {     echo "Index 0 does not exist"; }  if (isset($myArray[1])) {     echo $myArray[1]; } else {     echo "Index 1 does not exist"; }  print_r($myArray); // Shows only ['value'] => 10 and [10] => 20  ```  By using `isset()` or `array_key_exists()` you ensure that your code will handle non-existent array indices appropriately and prevent silent failures.